MySQL 

.Creating DB
    create database statement 
.Deleting an existing database 
    drop database 
.Creating a new table in a database
    create table 
        .column parameters specify the names of the table columns 
        .datatype parameter specifies the type of data the column can hold 
    .can also be completed by making a copy of an existing table - same column definitions & values from the original table 
.Drop/deleting an existing table from a database 
    .Truncate table - delete data inside a table 
.Altering a table 
    .changes the structure of a table 
        .adding, deleting, or modifying columns in an existing table 
        .adding or dropping various constraints on an existing table 
            .add/drop Primary key
    .cannot insert data values 

.Constraints
    .specify the rules for data in a table 
    .specified when the table is created or after (using alter table statement)
    .limit the type of data going into a table 
        .ensuring accuracy and reliability of the data in the table 
    .can be at table or column level 
  .common ones: .NOT NULL - ensures that a column cannot have a NULL value
                    .always contain a value
                    .cannot insert a new record, or update a record without adding a value 
                .UNIQUE - ensures that all values in a column are different 
                    .can be many unique constraints in a table 
                .PRIMARY KEY - combination of NOT NULL and UNIQUE; uniquely identifies each row in a table 
                .FOREIGN KEY - prevents actions that would destroy links between tables 
                .CHECK  - ensures that the values in a column satisfies a specific condition
                .DEFAULT - sets a default value for a column if no value is specified 
                .CREATE INDEX - used to create and retrieve data from the database very quickly 
